            <title>[AVRO-1409] Accurate method for evaluating schema compatibility</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1409</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1385&quot; title=&quot;Enum reader/writer resolution doesn&amp;#39;t report errors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1385&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1385&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it appears Avro&apos;s resolving decoder performs decode-time compatibility check, ie. per datum instance compatibility check, as opposed to per schema compatibility check.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For our use-cases, we need to determine whether all datum instances of a particular writer schema will always succeed in being decoded using a given reader schema.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
